    "This autonomous capability is part of why deep learning (DL), a subset of which includes DNNs, has historically diverged from traditional ML methods 17.",
    "Due to their enhanced efficacy in processing large-scale data sets, their ability to extract hidden valuable knowledge from data, and to employ specific pre-trained networks, DL models are therefore frequently used in medical imaging systems.",
